      <section id="id6207360">
        <title>[LO 2.1, LO 2.3, LO 2.4]</title>
        <section id="id6416168">
          <title>Light travels along a straight line.</title>
          <para id="id6259514">Light can change direction, though, and this happens in two ways:</para>
          <list id="id6259520" list-type="bulleted">
            <item>Refraction</item>
            <item>Reflection</item>
          </list>
          <para id="id6286573"><emphasis effect="bold">REFLECTION: </emphasis>We are going to look at reflection as it occurs with <emphasis effect="bold">mirrors. </emphasis></para>
          <para id="id6307751">When a beam of light arrives at a certain angle, it will be reflected at the same angle.</para>
          <para id="id4162528">ANGLE OF INCIDENCE = ANGLE OF REFLECTION</para>
          <table id="id8482042" summary="">
