      <para id="id3822287">Assignment 1:</para>
      <para id="id7290833">LIGHT</para>
      <list id="id7263358" list-type="bulleted">
        <item><emphasis effect="bold">LIGHT</emphasis> is another common type of energy.</item>
      </list>
      <list id="id7209742" list-type="bulleted">
        <item>You parents or teachers would like to have "eyes at the back of their heads" or would like you to believe that they see everything. We know that this is impossible, though, and for a simple reason</item>
      </list>
      <list id="id7181436" list-type="bulleted">
        <item>Light travels along a straight line. Light can change direction, though. This can be achieved in two ways:</item>
      </list>
      <para id="id6280778"/>
      <para id="id7219754">REFLECTION:</para>
      <list id="id7219758" list-type="bulleted">
        <item>We see this happening in the case of <emphasis effect="bold">mirrors.</emphasis></item>
      </list>
      <para id="id8869129">When a beam of light arrives at a certain angle, it will be reflected at the same angle.</para>
